00:09:30,344 --> 00:09:31,426
is healthy community.

165
00:09:32,578 --> 00:09:37,002
This doesn't necessarily mean just having, you know, a Discord server where people don't insult each other,

166
00:09:37,082 --> 00:09:44,588
but in general it means a long-term community is kind of the foundation of what your fan base can be for your studio,

167
00:09:44,668 --> 00:09:51,213
so any further titles already have a fair critical mass that is in a positive sense and want to support your work.

168
00:09:52,289 --> 00:09:56,650
Obviously having a healthy community also brings along many other advantages such as

169
00:09:56,770 --> 00:10:01,272
you know they can be your advocates, they can do a bunch of customer support on forums for you so

170
00:10:01,292 --> 00:10:04,493
you don't have to do it all yourself. If you're doing an early access period they might be

171
00:10:04,893 --> 00:10:08,194
contributing really meaningful ideas into game design and so on.

172
00:10:10,162 --> 00:10:12,424
So yeah, community is number one.

173
00:10:12,584 --> 00:10:14,505
We want a healthy, happy community.

